      <prop type="x-translation-ref">Analects XXXIII.33</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>子曰：「君子不可小知，而可大受也。小人不可大受，而可小知也。」</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The Master said, "The superior man cannot be known in little matters; but he may be intrusted with great concerns. The small man may not be intrusted with great concerns, but he may be known in little matters."</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
