      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>子曰：「民之於仁也，甚於水火。水火，吾見蹈而死者矣，未見蹈仁而死者也。」</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The Master said, "Virtue is more to man than either water or fire. I have seen men die from treading on water and fire, but I have never seen a man die from treading the course of virtue."</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
